{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δεσμός</b>, ὁ, <br /> <i>plural</i> δεσμά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Mercurium” 157, +others, 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 459, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.91 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], and so mostly in Trag., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 513, etc., and 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthyphro” 9a; but δεσμοί 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 525, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 518, 634, usually in 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus, as “Lg.” 793b, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: both forms in <i>Attic dialect</i> Inscrr., δεσμοί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 2.678 B 48, δεσμά [prev. work] 791.31,\">Refs</a>] the latter preferred by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.AD: Thomas Epigrammaticus Mag. p.79R. (_sing._ δεσμόν “SIG” 246 ii 36 (Delph.)\">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>], <i>Attic dialect</i> <i>accusative</i> to [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus): (δέω A)\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]:—<b>band, bond, anything for tying and fastening,</b> as <b>halter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.507 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>mooring-cable,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.100, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>door-latch,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 21.241 \">Refs</a>]; <b>yoke-strap,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.5.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, any <b>bond of union</b> or <b>connexion,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 31c, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the vowels, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Sph.” 253a \">Refs</a>]; δεσμοὶ πολιτείας, of the laws, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 793b \">Refs</a>]; εἰς τὰ δεσμοῦ for <b>binding material,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PTeb. 120.70 (1st c.BC). \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in <i>plural</i> (never δεσμά in this sense), <b>bonds, chains,</b> ἐκ δεσμῶν λυθῆναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 509, 770 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; πρὶν ἂν ἐξ ἀγρίων δ. χαλάσῃ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 177; ἐν δεσμοῖσι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 63; εἰς δεσμοὺς ἄγειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 518; δεσμοῖς 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.82 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ ἐπὶ τῶν δ., ={δεσμοφύλαξ}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Tox.” 29 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: in <i>singular</i>, collectively, <b>bonds, imprisonment,</b> δ. ἀχλυόεις epigram cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.77 (= “IG” 12.394); οὐδὲν ἄξιον δεσμοῦ 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.145; ἐν. δ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 958; ἐν δημοσίῳ δ. δεθείς 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 864e; ἔδησεν ἑαυτὸν τιμησάμενος δεσμοῦ 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 6.21 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i> of moral <b>bondage,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Abstinentia - Porphyrii Opuscula” 1.38, +others \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>ligature,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 495b13, +others \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> δ. ἄρθρου in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀγμῶν” 37 is explained by 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (at [prev. work]) as <b>ankylosis.</b> <br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>spell, charm,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"